tspan.tspan: Saint Paul Hymn to love, 1 Corinthians, 13 1-7
If I spoke in the tongues of men and angels,
and I would not have love,
I would be like noisy copper
If only I had the gift of prophesying
and he knew all the secrets,
and all [possible] faith, so that I may move
and I would not have love,
And if I would give alms all that I have,
and he set the body to be burned,
but I would not have love,
is not looking for his own
